calendar.description: Sets the default calendar system to use for interpreting and displaying dates throughout the plot.

valuecalendar.description: Sets the calendar system to use for `value`, if it is a date.

targetcalendar.description: Sets the calendar system to use for `target`, if it is an array of dates. If `target` is a string (eg *x*) we use the corresponding trace attribute (eg `xcalendar`) if it exists, even if `targetcalendar` is provided.
